Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 07:36:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] CLI: summarize completed M9 ingestion runs from persisted
 items and unify footer output

### Motivation

- Ensure the CLI shows accurate imported/failed/skipped counts for completed ingestion (M9) runs even when an `import_result` object is not returned, by deriving counts from persisted item statuses.
- Provide a consistent and explanatory footer for completed ingestion runs and preserve the existing validation-only (M8) footer when appropriate.

### Description

- Update `_print_import_run` to detect completed M9 run statuses and, when `import_result` is absent, compute a summary from persisted items and render a dedicated completed-ingestion footer using the new helpers.
- Add `_import_run_item_summary(run: ImportRun)` to derive `imported`, `failed`, and `skipped` counts from `run.items` and add `_print_completed_ingestion_footer(summary, *, run_status)` to centralize footer messaging.
- Introduce a `completed_m9_statuses` set (`{"succeeded", "partially_succeeded", "failed"}`) to distinguish completed ingestion runs from validation-only runs and adjust control flow to return early after printing the appropriate footer.
- Update `tests/test_cli.py` to reflect the new messages and add multiple tests and a helper (`_persist_import_run_with_item_statuses`) that verify M8 vs M9 behavior, full/partial/failed/skipped summaries, and that the validation-only footer is preserved; also normalize a test string literal for an error message.

### Testing

- Ran the CLI unit tests in `tests/test_cli.py`, including new tests `test_corpus_run_show_preserves_m8_validation_only_footer`, `test_corpus_run_show_summarizes_successful_m9_import`, `test_corpus_run_show_summarizes_partial_success_m9_import`, `test_corpus_run_show_summarizes_failed_m9_import_with_zero_imports`, and `test_corpus_run_show_summarizes_all_skipped_successful_m9_import`; all tests passed.
- Updated `test_corpus_import_command_reports_successful_import` assertions to expect the new aggregated footer lines and confirmed the test succeeds.
